deviceType.name: deviceType
deviceType.description: This object defines the board type for the Management board in the device. (eg. IRBM, IRM). See appendix A for values.

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: An ASCII name of the device that this agent manages.

deviceIPAddress.name: deviceIPAddress
deviceIPAddress.description: The Internet address of this device. Write access is granted only if SuperUser access is used.

currentTime.name: currentTime
currentTime.description: The current time of day as measured by the device in HHMMSS format.

currentDate.name: currentDate
currentDate.description: The current date as measured by the device in MMDDYYYY format.

mACAddress.name: mACAddress
mACAddress.description: The MAC (Ethernet) address of the MMAC. This can also be obtained from address translation MIB.

deviceSlots.name: deviceSlots
deviceSlots.description: Number of available slots in this device including the IRM slot.

deviceOccupiedSlots.name: deviceOccupiedSlots
deviceOccupiedSlots.description: The slots that contain MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (eg. If a bit is set then that board is present. For example, a value of 3 indicates that there are boards in the IRM slot and the first MIM slot.

devicePortsOn.name: devicePortsOn
devicePortsOn.description: A read will return the number of adminstratively ON ports for the device. A write of a 1 will administratively enable all the ports on the device, except for redundant ports.

deviceTotalPorts.name: deviceTotalPorts
deviceTotalPorts.description: The total number of ports in the MMAC.

deviceTotalPkts.name: deviceTotalPkts
deviceTotalPkts.description: The number of packets detected on all ports of this device.

deviceTotalErrors.name: deviceTotalErrors
deviceTotalErrors.description: The sum of all alignment, CRC, out-of-window collisions, runt, and giant errors detected by this device.

deviceTransmitColls.name: deviceTransmitColls
deviceTransmitColls.description: The number of transmit collisions detected by this device.

deviceRecColls.name: deviceRecColls
deviceRecColls.description: The number of receive collsions detected by this device.

deviceAligns.name: deviceAligns
deviceAligns.description: The number of packets with alignment errors detected by this device.

deviceCRCs.name: deviceCRCs
deviceCRCs.description: The number of packets with bad CRC detected by this device.

deviceRunts.name: deviceRunts
deviceRunts.description: The number of runt frames detected by this device.

deviceOOWColls.name: deviceOOWColls
deviceOOWColls.description: The number of out-of-window collisions detected by this device.

deviceNoResources.name: deviceNoResources
deviceNoResources.description: The number of no resource condtions detected by this device.

deviceRecBytes.name: deviceRecBytes
deviceRecBytes.description: The number of bytes detected on the network by this device.

deviceGiantFrames.name: deviceGiantFrames
deviceGiantFrames.description: The number of longer than 1518 byte packets detected by this device.

deviceRestart.name: deviceRestart
deviceRestart.description: A read will return 0. A set of 0 will restart the device.

deviceResetCounters.name: deviceResetCounters
deviceResetCounters.description: A read will return 0. A set of 0 will reset all the counters for the device, boards and ports.

deviceRedundantCts.name: deviceRedundantCts
deviceRedundantCts.description: The number of redundant circuits available for use.

deviceTimeBase.name: deviceTimeBase
deviceTimeBase.description: The number of seconds used as the interval for performing all of the rate alarm checks. The minimum is 10 secs. There isn't a maximum.

deviceResetRedundancy.name: deviceResetRedundancy
deviceResetRedundancy.description: A read will return 0. A set of a 1 will reset redundancy for the entire box.

deviceSrcAddrAgingTime.name: deviceSrcAddrAgingTime
deviceSrcAddrAgingTime.description: The number of minutes that a source address is not detected before it is removed from the source address table. The minimum is 1 minute and the maximum is 1440 minutes (max minutes in a day).

deviceSrcAddrTraps.name: deviceSrcAddrTraps
deviceSrcAddrTraps.description: Controls sending of source address related traps.

deviceSrcAddrLocked.name: deviceSrcAddrLocked
deviceSrcAddrLocked.description: A set of 2 will disable all ports that support link status but do not have link active, or is segmented. The first source address seen on each of the remaining enabled ports, that have the type of station, will be the only address allowed through that port. If any other address is seen the port will be disabled.

deviceEnetBoardMap.name: deviceEnetBoardMap
deviceEnetBoardMap.description: The slots that contain Ethernet MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (e.g. If a bit is set then that board is present and is an Ethernet MIM.) For example, a value of 3 indicates that there are boards in the IRM slot and the first MIM slot and that these boards are Ethernet MIMs.

deviceTokenRingBoardMap.name: deviceTokenRingBoardMap
deviceTokenRingBoardMap.description: The slots that contain Token Ring MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (e.g. If a bit is set then that board is present and is a Token Ring MIM.) For example, a value of 2 indicates that there is a board in the first slot and it is a Token Ring board.

deviceFDDIBoardMap.name: deviceFDDIBoardMap
deviceFDDIBoardMap.description: The slots that contain FDDI MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (e.g. If a bit is set then that board is present and is a FDDI MIM.) For example, a value of 2 indicates that there is a board in the first slot and it is a FDDI board.

deviceRestoreDefaults.name: deviceRestoreDefaults
deviceRestoreDefaults.description: A get will return 0. A set of 0 will restore all of battery backed RAM to factory defaults, with the execption of the IP address, the community table and the modem baud rate.

deviceActiveUsers.name: deviceActiveUsers
deviceActiveUsers.description: The number of active users seen on this device.

deviceBroadPkts.name: deviceBroadPkts
deviceBroadPkts.description: The sum of all of the broadcast packets detected on all ports of this device.

deviceMultPkts.name: deviceMultPkts
deviceMultPkts.description: The sum of all of the multicast packets detected on all ports of this device.

deviceThdPartyOccupiedSlots.name: deviceThdPartyOccupiedSlots
deviceThdPartyOccupiedSlots.description: The slots that contain Third Party MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (eg. if a bit is set then that board is present and is a Third Party MIM.) For example, a value of 4 indicates that there is a board in the third MIM slot (slot 4) and that this board is a Third Party MIM.

deviceImimOccupiedSlots.name: deviceImimOccupiedSlots
deviceImimOccupiedSlots.description: The slots that contain IMIM boards. This field is bit encoded (eg. if a bit is set then that board is present and is an IMIM). For example, a value of 4 indicates that there is a board in the third MIM slot (slot 4) and that this board is an IMIM.

deviceLinkTraps.name: deviceLinkTraps
deviceLinkTraps.description: Controls sending of link related traps.

deviceSegTraps.name: deviceSegTraps
deviceSegTraps.description: Controls sending of seg related traps.

ctIPDefaultFrameType.name: ctIPDefaultFrameType
ctIPDefaultFrameType.description: Defines the default frame type that will be used by the device. A device will understand both frame types and will respond based upon the framing type that is learned for the given address. This object defines the type of framing that will be used if no framing is known, for example ARP requests. Setting a value of 8022snap(2) will result in framing 802.3 - 802.2 - IP packets being generated by default. Setting a value of ethernet(1) will result in framing ethernet IP packets by default.

sourceAddrBoard.name: sourceAddrBoard
sourceAddrBoard.description: The board number of the port that the supplied source address has been seen on.

sourceAddrPort.name: sourceAddrPort
sourceAddrPort.description: The port number of the port that the supplied source address has been seen on.

redundancyPollInterval.name: redundancyPollInterval
redundancyPollInterval.description: The number of seconds between polls for redundancy. The minimum is 0 and the maximum is 99.

redundancyTestTod.name: redundancyTestTod
redundancyTestTod.description: The time of day at which the redundant circuits should be tested.

redundancyPerformTest.name: redundancyPerformTest
redundancyPerformTest.description: A read will return a 0. A set of a 1 will test the redundant circuits now.

redundancyCircuitName.name: redundancyCircuitName
redundancyCircuitName.description: The name of the indicated circuit.

redundancyRetryCount.name: redundancyRetryCount
redundancyRetryCount.description: The number of unanswered polls allowed for the indicated circuit before the current connection is declared bad. The minimum is 0 the maximum is 16.

redundancyNumBPs.name: redundancyNumBPs
redundancyNumBPs.description: The number of board/port combinations associated with the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitBoards.name: redundancyCircuitBoards
redundancyCircuitBoards.description: The boards associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index. Note: The instance identifier for this object is the circuit number followed by an index. The index has no other meaning than to be used as an index for the purposes of the GET NEXT operation.

redundancyCircuitPort.name: redundancyCircuitPort
redundancyCircuitPort.description: The ports associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index. Note: The instance identifier for this object is the circuit number followed by an index. The index has no other meaning than to be used as an index for the purposes of the GET NEXT operation.

redundancyCircuitTypes.name: redundancyCircuitTypes
redundancyCircuitTypes.description: The type of each port associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index. Note: The instance identifier for this object is the circuit number followed by an index. The index has no other meaning than to be used as an index for the purposes of the GET NEXT operation.

redundancyCircuitNumAddr.name: redundancyCircuitNumAddr
redundancyCircuitNumAddr.description: The number of addresses associated with the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitMACAddrAdd.name: redundancyCircuitMACAddrAdd
redundancyCircuitMACAddrAdd.description: A get will return a null string. A set adds an ethernet address to the polling list for the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitMACAddrDel.name: redundancyCircuitMACAddrDel
redundancyCircuitMACAddrDel.description: A get will return a null string. A set deletes an ethernet address from the polling list for the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitMACAddrDisp.name: redundancyCircuitMACAddrDisp
redundancyCircuitMACAddrDisp.description: The ethernet addresses associated with the indicated circuit, accessed by index. Note: The instance identifier for this object is the circuit number followed by an index. The index has no other meaning than to be used as an index for the purposes of the GET NEXT operation.

redundancyCircuitEnable.name: redundancyCircuitEnable
redundancyCircuitEnable.description: Enables and disables the indicated circuit.

redundancyCircuitReset.name: redundancyCircuitReset
redundancyCircuitReset.description: A get will return 0. A set of 1 will reset the indicated circuit, return all of the associated board and ports to NOT-USED, remove associated addresses from the polling list, reset the circuit name and retry count to default values.

devTrafficEnable.name: devTrafficEnable
devTrafficEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for device level traffic thresholds getting exceeded.

devTrafficThreshold.name: devTrafficThreshold
devTrafficThreshold.description: The number of packets detected by the device within the device timebase that will cause a device traffic alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 0. There isn't a maximum.

devCollsEnable.name: devCollsEnable
devCollsEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for device level collision thresholds getting exceeded.

devCollsThreshold.name: devCollsThreshold
devCollsThreshold.description: The number of collisions per good packet detected by the device within the device timebase that will cause a device collision alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 1, the maximum is 15.

devErrorEnable.name: devErrorEnable
devErrorEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for device level error thresholds getting exceeded.

devErrorThreshold.name: devErrorThreshold
devErrorThreshold.description: The percentage of errors per good packet detected by the device within the device timebase that will cause a device error alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 1, the maximum is 100.

devErrorSource.name: devErrorSource
devErrorSource.description: The type of errors used for the device error alarm. The INTEGER is a bit encoded version of which errors to include in the error sum. The bits are encoded as follows: CRC_errors - Bit 0 - Least Significant Bit runts - Bit 1 OOW_colls - Bit 2 align_errs - Bit 3 No_resource - Bit 4 Giants - Bit 5

devBroadEnable.name: devBroadEnable
devBroadEnable.description: Enable the sending of device level broadcast traps.

devBroadThreshold.name: devBroadThreshold
devBroadThreshold.description: The threshold of broadcast packets within the Devicetimebase that will cause a broadcast alarm.

bdTrafficEnable.name: bdTrafficEnable
bdTrafficEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for board level traffic thresholds getting exceeded.

bdTrafficThreshold.name: bdTrafficThreshold
bdTrafficThreshold.description: The number of packets detected by the specified board within the device timebase that will cause a board traffic alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 0. There isn't a maximum.

bdTrafficBdDisable.name: bdTrafficBdDisable
bdTrafficBdDisable.description: Permits a board to be disabled on a traffic threshold getting exceeded.

bdCollsEnable.name: bdCollsEnable
bdCollsEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for board level collision thresholds getting exceeded.

bdCollsThreshold.name: bdCollsThreshold
bdCollsThreshold.description: The number of collisions per good packet detected by the specified board within the device timebase that will cause a board collision alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 1, the maximum is 15.

bdCollsBdDisable.name: bdCollsBdDisable
bdCollsBdDisable.description: Permits a board to be disabled on a collision threshold getting exceeded.

bdErrorEnable.name: bdErrorEnable
bdErrorEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for board level error thresholds getting exceeded.

bdErrorThreshold.name: bdErrorThreshold
bdErrorThreshold.description: The percentage of errors per good packet detected by the specified board within the device timebase that will cause a board error alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 1, the maximum is 100.

bdErrorSource.name: bdErrorSource
bdErrorSource.description: The type of errors used for the board error alarm. The INTEGER is a bit encoded version of which errors to include in the error sum. The bits are encoded as follows: CRC_errors - Bit 0 - Least Significant Bit runts - Bit 1 OOW_colls - Bit 2 align_errs - Bit 3 No_resource - Bit 4 Giants - Bit 5

bdErrorBdDisable.name: bdErrorBdDisable
bdErrorBdDisable.description: Permits a board to be disabled on an error threshold getting exceeded.

bdBroadEnable.name: bdBroadEnable
bdBroadEnable.description: Enable the sending of board level broadcast traps for this board.

bdBroadThreshold.name: bdBroadThreshold
bdBroadThreshold.description: The threshold of broadcast packets within the Devicetimebase that will cause a broadcast alarm.

bdBroadDisable.name: bdBroadDisable
bdBroadDisable.description: Permit a board to be disabled on a broadcast threshold alarm.

portTrafficEnable.name: portTrafficEnable
portTrafficEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for port level traffic thresholds getting exceeded.

portTrafficThreshold.name: portTrafficThreshold
portTrafficThreshold.description: The number of packets detected by the specified port within the device timebase that will cause a port traffic alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 0. There isn't a maximum.

portTrafficPortDisable.name: portTrafficPortDisable
portTrafficPortDisable.description: Permits a port to be disabled on a traffic threshold getting exceeded.

portCollsEnable.name: portCollsEnable
portCollsEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for port level collision thresholds getting exceeded.

portCollsThreshold.name: portCollsThreshold
portCollsThreshold.description: The number of collisions per good packet detected by the specified port within the device timebase that will cause a port collision alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 1, the maximum is 15.

portCollsPortDisable.name: portCollsPortDisable
portCollsPortDisable.description: Permits a port to be disabled on a collision threshold getting exceeded.

portErrorEnable.name: portErrorEnable
portErrorEnable.description: Enable or disable the checking for port level error thresholds getting exceeded.

portErrorThreshold.name: portErrorThreshold
portErrorThreshold.description: The percentage of errors per good packet detected by the specified port within the device timebase that will cause a port error alarm trap to be sent. The minimum is 1, the maximum is 100.

portErrorSource.name: portErrorSource
portErrorSource.description: The type of errors used for the port error alarm. The INTEGER is a bit encoded version of which errors to include in the error sum. The bits are encoded as follows: CRC_errors - Bit 0 - Least Significant Bit runts - Bit 1 OOW_colls - Bit 2 align_errs - Bit 3 No_resource - Bit 4 Giants - Bit 5

portErrorPortDisable.name: portErrorPortDisable
portErrorPortDisable.description: Permits a port to be disabled on an error threshold getting exceeded.

portBroadEnable.name: portBroadEnable
portBroadEnable.description: Enable the sending of port level broadcast alarms.

portBroadThreshold.name: portBroadThreshold
portBroadThreshold.description: The threshold of broadcast packets within the Devicetimebase that will cause a broadcast alarm.

portBroadDisable.name: portBroadDisable
portBroadDisable.description: Permit a port to be disabled on a broadcast threshold alarm.

deviceTRTokenRingPortsOn.name: deviceTRTokenRingPortsOn
deviceTRTokenRingPortsOn.description: The number of Token Ring Ports (i.e. station, Ring In and Ring Out ports) administratively ON for this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingPorts.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingPorts
deviceTRTotalTokenRingPorts.description: The total number of Token Ring Ports (i.e. station, Ring In and Ring Out ports) on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPortsOn.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPortsOn
deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPortsOn.description: The total number of Ring In and Ring Out ports (active) administratively ON for this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPorts.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPorts
deviceTRTotalTokenRingRingPorts.description: The total number of Ring In and Ring Out ports on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingRings.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingRings
deviceTRTotalTokenRingRings.description: The total number of (Token Ring) rings formed on this device.

deviceTRTotalTokenRingBoards.name: deviceTRTotalTokenRingBoards
deviceTRTotalTokenRingBoards.description: The total number of Token Ring MIMs in the MMAC.

deviceTRTokenRingBoardMap.name: deviceTRTokenRingBoardMap
deviceTRTokenRingBoardMap.description: The slots that contain Token Ring MIM boards. This field is bit encoded (e.g. If a bit is set then that board is present and is a Token Ring MIM.) For example, a value of 2 indicates that there is a board in the first slot and it is a Token Ring board.

boardIndex.name: boardIndex

boardName.description: The name of the board. This field will only contain printable ASCII characters.

boardType.name: boardType
boardType.description: The type of the MIM. (eg. FOT, TPT, etc). See appendix A for encoding.

boardTotalPorts.description: Total number of ports supported on this board.

boardPortsOn.name: boardPortsOn
boardPortsOn.description: A read will return the number of adminstratively ON ports for the board. A write of a 2 will administratively enable all the ports on the board, except for redundant ports.

boardActiveUsers.name: boardActiveUsers
boardActiveUsers.description: The number of active users seen on this board.

boardGiants.name: boardGiants

boardBroadPkts.description: The number broadcast packets detected by this board.

boardMultPkts.name: boardMultPkts
boardMultPkts.description: The number multicast packets detected by this board.

boardTotalRingPorts.name: boardTotalRingPorts
boardTotalRingPorts.description: The total number of ring ports on this board. Currently, zero or two.

boardTotalStationPorts.name: boardTotalStationPorts
boardTotalStationPorts.description: The total number of station ports on this board.

boardTotalRingPortsOn.name: boardTotalRingPortsOn
boardTotalRingPortsOn.description: The number of administartively ON ring ports on this board.

boardTotalStationPortsOn.name: boardTotalStationPortsOn
boardTotalStationPortsOn.description: The number of administartively ON station ports on this board.

boardRingSpeedFault.description: Data speed of station mismatches configuration speed of board. Board is automatically bypassed.

boardFirstRingPort.name: boardFirstRingPort
boardFirstRingPort.description: The port number of the first ring port.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: The number of this port relative to the board it is on.

portMediaType.name: portMediaType
portMediaType.description: The type of the port. (eg. FOT, TPT, etc). See appendix A for values.

portAdminState.name: portAdminState
portAdminState.description: The administrative status of this port.

portSourceAddr.name: portSourceAddr
portSourceAddr.description: A source address that has been seen on this port.

portActiveUsers.name: portActiveUsers
portActiveUsers.description: The number of active users seen on this port.

portTopologyType.name: portTopologyType
portTopologyType.description: The topological type of the port. Station referring to a port that has seen 1 or 0 addresses. Trunk referring to a port that has seen more than 1 address.

portLinkStatus.description: The state of the link signal for this port

portStatus.name: portStatus

portGiantFrames.name: portGiantFrames

portRedundCrt.description: The redundant circuit with which this port is associated.

portRedundType.description: The type of port this port is in the redundant circuit.

portRedundStatus.description: The current state of this port in the redundant circuit.

portForceTrunkType.description: This variable forces a port to be a trunk port.

portBroadPkts.description: The sum of broadcast packets detected on this port.

portMultPkts.description: The sum of multicast packets detected on this port.

stationPortLinkStatus.name: stationPortLinkStatus
stationPortLinkStatus.description: When station is supplying phantom current the Link Signal is active. When there is no phantom current the Link Signal is inactive.

stationPortLinkStateTime.name: stationPortLinkStateTime
stationPortLinkStateTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) elapsed since the station port last changed state. A write of 0 will reset the elapsed time.

targetRevision.name: targetRevision
targetRevision.description: The revision of the target board.

targetPortAssociation.name: targetPortAssociation
targetPortAssociation.description: Controls how the front panel ports are associated with the bridge or the repeater. The valid values are: Value AUI Port Fiber Port 0 Bridge Redundant 1 Redundant Bridge 2 Bridge Repeater 3 Repeater Bridge 4 Redundant Repeater 5 Repeater Redundant Note: only values 0 and 1 are valid for rev 2 boards and before. Note: only values 4 and 5 are valid for the IRM2.

fnbConnectedLeft.name: fnbConnectedLeft
fnbConnectedLeft.description: The Connected Left board (board n + 1) has the following states: Detached == 1 (Management (only management) detached, read/write). Attached == 2 (Management/AutoMode attached, read/write). Faulted == 3 (Management/AutoMode tried to attach but failed read ONLY).

fnbConnectedRight.name: fnbConnectedRight
fnbConnectedRight.description: The Connected Right board (board n - 1) has the following states: Detached == 1 (Management (only management) detached, read/write). Attached == 2 (Management/AutoMode attached, read/write). Faulted == 3 (Management/AutoMode tried to attach but failed read ONLY).

audibleAlarmEnable.name: audibleAlarmEnable
audibleAlarmEnable.description: Allows/disallows the audible alarm to be sounded when a situation occurs that the alarm should be sounded.

audibleAlarmOff.name: audibleAlarmOff
audibleAlarmOff.description: Turn off a sounding alarm. A read will tell you if the alarm is on or not. A write will stop a sounding alarm.
